         <abstract>
            <p>An algorithm used to evaluate double sums arising in a model describing the nematic phase behavior of surfactant solutions is demonstrated to yield approximations accurate to within a tenth of a percent. When direct summation would converge slowly, an asymptotic result is employed based on a double application of the Euler-Maclaurin sum formula.</p>
          </abstract>
